AHCPR ROUNDUP

The agency has announced three public meetings at which individuals and
organizations may address practice guideline panel members:

o Screening for Alzheimer's disease and other related dementias -- Apr. 12,
  Hyatt Regency Washington, Washington DC. For information: Demie Lyons,
  617/290-0090

o Diagnosis and treatment of chest pain due to unstable angina, Apr. 8,
  American College of Cardiology, Heart House, Bethesda MD. For
  information: Nancy Archibald, 919/684-6077

o Quality determinants of mammography, Mar. 8, Bethesda Marriott, Bethesda
  MD. For information: Mary Madison, 617/290-0090.

o The Agency announced a request for proposals for health care financing
  and cost research in the Jan. 29 NIH Guide. For information: Michael
  Hagen, 301/227-8354.




