GLAXO WELLCOME ANNOUNCES LAUNCH OF BOND

Glaxo Wellcome has announced the launch of a $500 million fixed rate
bond due 25 January 2006. The issue is priced at a spread of 48 basis
points over the yield on the 5.875 per cent US Treasury Bond due
November 2005. Proceeds are to be used to repay debts and for general
corporate purposes, says the company. Lehman Bros and JP Morgan
Securities Ltd are joint lead managers for the issue.



