NORTH KOREAN JUDGES LIKELY TO VISIT SEOUL+

     SEOUL, DEC. 23 KYODO - TWO NORTH KOREAN ICE HOCKEY JUDGES WILL
ATTEND AN INSTITUTE CLASS FOR JUDGES NEXT FEBRUARY IN SEOUL, THE
YONHAP NEWS AGENCY REPORTED SATURDAY.
     THE REPORT SAID THE FIRST VISIT BY NORTH KOREAN SPORTS PEOPLE TO
SOUTH KOREA SINCE THE KOREAN PENINSULA WAS DIVIDED IN 1948 WAS
CONFIRMED IN A TELEGRAM SENT BY THE INTERNATIONAL ICE HOCKEY
FEDERATION TO THE SOUTH KOREAN ICE HOCKEY ASSOCIATION.
     THE REPORT SAID THE INSTITUTE CLASS IS REQUIRED BEFORE THE
EXPECTED VARIOUS INTERNATIONAL COMPETITIONS OF THE SPORT NEXT YEAR,
SO THE JUDGES ARE EXPECTED TO ATTEND.
     NORTH KOREA WILL HOST THE THIRD WINTER ASIAN GAMES IN 1995 AND
THIS ALSO WILL WORK IN FAVOR OF SUCH A TRIP TO SEOUL, THE REPORT
ADDED.



