Disclosure compliance

     Baltimore City Council members Agnes Welch and Martin
O'Malley filed tardy campaign finance disclosure reports and paid
fines for missing the deadlines just in time for their December 7
inaugurations, the Baltimore Sun reported.
     Under Maryland law, elected state and local officials cannot
be sworn into office without certification by the State
Administrative Board of Election Laws that all disclosure reports
have been filed and all fines have been paid.



