ELSEVIER SELLS STAKE IN WOLTERS KLUWER TO GOLDMAN SACHS

Elsevier (Amsterdam, Neth.) has sold its 33% stake in
Wolters Kluwer (Deventer, Neth.) to Goldman, Sachs & Co.
(New York). Goldman, Sachs said that it has arranged to
sell half of that investment to individual investors. The
stock involved in the deal is worth about $520 million.




