<A NAME = "25"></A>Copyright
THE BUSINESS PUBLISHER via NewsNet
December 15, 1990

"NIKKEI BUSINESS" TO INCREASE FREQUENCY

Japan's largest professional publication, "Nikkei
Business," published by Nikkei Business Publications
(Tokyo) will increase frequency to weekly from 24 times a
year. The company said that the change was necessary to
meet the "rapid changes on the international business
environment as represented by the unification of Germany
and the invasion of Kuwait" and to adapt to the new
Japanese business practice of adopting five-day workweeks.




